determines risk/discovery trade-off<br/><br/>NEED UPDATE (Convergence Law):<br/>  Need(t+1) = max(0, Need(t) - Received(t))<br/>  → Needs decrease as satisfied, ensuring convergence<br/><br/>EMA LEARNING RATE:<br/>  α = 0.2 (weights last ~5 observations)<br/>  Higher α = faster learning, more volatile<br/>  Lower α = slower learning, more stable<br/>  → Trade-off between responsiveness and stability
